Since 2001, the Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations (FAO) has designated June 1 as World Milk Day (WMD). The day recognizes the role of dairy in nutrition, rural incomes, and sustainability, all important components of the Feed the Future Bangladesh Livestock Production for Improved Nutrition project. This year, in celebration of WMD, we invite photo submissions showcasing one of the WMD themes, including: Contest partner Shwapno has donated retail vouchers totaling 40,000 BDT for the top three entries, including: Submit your photo and read the rules in full here.